Sentencas: Nano-crystalline Nd1.8Ce0.2CuO4+ synthesized by combusting mixed precursor materials under microwave heating followed by sintering at 1000 degrees C for 4h exhibits highest dc conductivity (sigma=2.50S/cm at 700 degrees C) due to lowest crystallite size (50nm), which compared with preparation by conventional combustion and solid-state reaction.
Titulo: Effect of Synthesis Route on Electrical and Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.8Ce0.2CuO4+ Cathode Material for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Symmetric cells configured as electrode/electrolyte/electrode were fabricated by spin coating.
Titulo: Effect of Synthesis Route on Electrical and Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.8Ce0.2CuO4+ Cathode Material for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The lowest area specific resistance (ASR) value of 0.50cm(2) was obtained at a temperature 700 degrees C. Morphology of cathode material is largely dependent on the preparative route, and that influences ASR.
Titulo: Effect of Synthesis Route on Electrical and Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.8Ce0.2CuO4+ Cathode Material for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Low frequency complex impedance curve was modeled by Gerischer element.
Titulo: Effect of Synthesis Route on Electrical and Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.8Ce0.2CuO4+ Cathode Material for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance suggested absorption of oxygen by the Nd1.8Ce0.2CuO4+ lattice.
Titulo: Effect of Synthesis Route on Electrical and Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.8Ce0.2CuO4+ Cathode Material for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Combustion of precursors using microwave heating promises to be a potential route for materials preparation to achieve improved electrochemical performance of cathode in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell applications.
Titulo: Effect of Synthesis Route on Electrical and Electrochemical Performance of Nd1.8Ce0.2CuO4+ Cathode Material for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
